title: Brexit votes in the United Kingdom by social class 2016
summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 4 different Responses for 2 groups Remain, and Leave that are presented on the X-axis.
Response Upper Working-Class (C2) had the maximum SOME LABEL among all 2 groups, and it was for Leave. The minimum SOME LABEL was observed in Response Lower Working-Class (DE) for Remain.
Among all the Responses, Leave had the highest SOME LABEL 64.0 in Response Upper Working-Class (C2) and lowest value 43.0 in Response Upper Middle-Class (AB).
The maximum SOME LABEL for Leave that was found in Response Upper Working-Class (C2) was 1.49 times larger than the minimum SOME LABEL observed in Response Upper Middle-Class (AB).

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 4 different Responses on X-axis for 2 groups Remain, and Leave. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding SOME LABEL.
Response Upper Working-Class (C2) had the maximum SOME LABEL among all 2 groups, and it was for Leave. The minimum SOME LABEL was observed in Response Lower Working-Class (DE) for Remain.
In Response Upper Working-Class (C2), Leave had the highest SOME LABEL among all 4 Responses and it has the lowest SOME LABEL in Response Upper Middle-Class (AB).
Response Upper Working-Class (C2) and Upper Middle-Class (AB) had the biggest gap of 21.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for Leave.
Among the groups, Remain had the biggest difference in SOME LABEL. Where the maximum SOME LABEL was 1.58 times larger than the minimum SOME LABEL.
Averaging all 2 groups Remain, and Leave, the Response Upper Middle-Class (AB) is the maximum SOME LABEL and Lower Working-Class (DE) is the minimum SOME LABEL.
